1. Download SRA file using prefetch:
prefetch -v SRR10911462

2. Convert SRA to paired-end gzipped FASTQ files using fasterq-dump:
fasterq-dump --split-files --threads 6 SRR10911462 -O ./fastq/
gzip ./fastq/SRR10911462_*.fastq

3. Quality trimming with CLC Genomics Workbench.

4. Build HISAT2 genome index (assuming reference genome fasta genome.fa):
hisat2-build -p 8 genome.fa OmyK2

5. Align paired-end reads to genome:
hisat2 -p 8 -x OmyK2 \
  -1 ./fastq/SRR10911462_1.fastq.gz \
  -2 ./fastq/SRR10911462_2.fastq.gz \
  -S SRR10911462_aligned.sam \
  --summary-file SRR10911462_alignment_summary.txt

6. Convert SAM to sorted BAM and index using samtools:
samtools view -b SRR10911462_aligned.sam > SRR10911462_aligned.bam
samtools sort -@ 8 SRR10911462_aligned.bam -o SRR10911462_aligned.sorted.bam
samtools index SRR10911462_aligned.sorted.bam

7. Expression quantification "calculate TPM for multiple bam files in a directory"
TPMCalculator -g ref_annotation.gtf -d /home/salemlab/Documents/Bam/ -t transcript_id -e -a
